1 A BILL for an Act to amend and reenact sections 49-17.1-02, 49-17.1-03, and 49-17.1-04 of the
2 North Dakota Century Code, relating to rail service assistance.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Section 49-17.1-02 of the North Dakota Century Code is
5 amended and reenacted as follows:
6 49-17.1-02. Department of transportation as designated state agency.
7 The department, with the approvalcooperation of the commission, is authorized to exercise
8 those powers necessary for the state to qualify for rail service assistance grants pursuant to
9 provisions of the Railroad Revitalization and Regulatory Reform Act of 1976 [Pub. L. 94-210; 90
10 Stat. 149; 49 U.S.C. 1651 et seq.], including authority to:
11 1. Prepare and recommend a state plan for all rail transportation and local rail services.
12 2. Administer and coordinate the state plan.
13 3. Provide in the plan for the equitable distribution of rail service assistance grants
14 among state, local, and regional transportation authorities.
15 4. Promote and support safe, adequate, and efficient rail services for those railway lines
16 receiving rail service assistance grants.
17 5. Employ sufficient trained and qualified personnel for these purposes.
18 6. Maintain adequate programs of investigation, research, promotion, and development
19 in connection with these purposes and to provide for public participation therein.
20 7. Provide satisfactory assurances on behalf of the state that fiscal control and fund
21 accounting procedures will be adopted by the state as may be necessary to assure
22 proper disbursement of an account for federal funds paid to the state as rail service
23 assistance grants.
