6 SECTION 2. AMENDMENT. Section 49-17.1-03 of the North Dakota Century Code is
7 amended and reenacted as follows:
8 49-17.1-03. Application for assistance.
9 The department, with the approval of the commission, may make application on behalf of
10 the state for grants made available by the secretary of transportation under the Railroad
11 Revitalization and Regulatory Reform Act of 1976 [Pub. L. 94-210; 90 Stat. 149; 49 U.S.C.
12 1651 et seq.].
13 SECTION 3. AMENDMENT. Section 49-17.1-04 of the North Dakota Century Code is
14 amended and reenacted as follows:
15 49-17.1-04. Use of public and private funds - Public service commission participation.
16 The department, with the approvalcooperation of the commission, may utilize public and
17 private funds appropriated by the legislative assembly in carrying out the purpose of this
18 chapter. The department shall cooperate with the commission and with other states in the
19 reorganization or reopening of any railway line which may have been abandoned by any railway
20 corporation providing railway services within the state. In carrying out the authority conferred by
21 this section, the department may enter into agreements, contracts, or other arrangements with
22 the necessary parties to accomplish the purposes of this chapter.
